Preheat your oven to 220°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips, then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Halve the @bell pepper{1}, discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces and pop them onto another baking tray. Drizzle all the veg with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out. When your oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf and the pepper on the middle shelf until soft, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half. Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch the almonds like a hawk as they can burn easily. When the almonds have toasted, transfer them to a #bowl{} (keep the pan, we will use it again).

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of oil. When the oil is hot, add the @capers{15} and @raisins{40} and cook for ~{30%seconds}, stirring. Then add the @red wine vinegar{12} and cook until it has almost all evaporated. Next, add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}, @vegetable stock paste{10}, cannellini beans, @water for the sauce{75}, @sugar{1.5} and half the @dried oregano{1} to the pan. Season with salt and pepper, stir to combine. Bring up to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

While the stew simmers, combine the garlic, remaining dried oregano and the @olive oil{2} for the garlic bread in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Lay the ciabatta onto a baking tray, cut-side up. Drizzle the garlic-herb oil on top. Pop the garlic bread into your oven until nicely toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the roasted veg. Taste and add more salt or pepper if needed. Allow it to simmer for a further ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove it from the heat.

When everything is ready, divide the aubergine and pepper caponata stew between your #bowls{}. Garnish with a sprinkling of the flaked almonds. Cut the garlic bread into triangles and serve alongside for dipping and scooping. Enjoy!